Offer is valid only on stock lenses BC8.5 from -0,75 to -8,0.  Acuvue Oasys 1-Day with HydraLuxe™ contact lenses, from healthcare specialists Johnson & Johnson, are daily disposable lenses that use advanced technology for a truly comfortable wearing experience. HydraLuxe™ technology uses a coating around the lens surface that reduces the symptoms of tired eyes and helps to prevent them from becoming dry and irritated.

    Acuvue Oasys 1-Day with HydraLuxe™ work to form a tear-like network throughout the lens that helps your natural tears to maintain their moisture during wear. This ensures that your eyes remain hydrated and feeling natural throughout the day, as if you weren't wearing contact lenses at all. With an added UV filter, these lenses also offer an extra level of protection against harmful exposure to the sun and have a handling tint for easy application, making them ideal for first-time wearers. Lenses are available in two base curves BC 8.5 and BC 9.0.

  4. Biotrue ONEday 30 pcs

    Biotrue ONEday is the latest in cutting-edge technology from the eye care professionals at Bausch and Lomb. Designed to mimic the human eye's natural surface this is a daily contact lens that provides outstanding all day comfort. Made from hypergel; the next generation in contact lens material it contains exactly 78% water, this number is important because it's the same amount of water the human cornea holds. The hypergel surface is designed to copy the lipid tear film ensuring moisture is retained throughout wear so that eyes don't become dry or irritated and feel as natural as if you weren't wearing lenses at all.

    The unique design of Biotrue ONEday has proven itself to be outstanding, even when up against the leading daily disposables on the market. In a recent study by Bausch and Lomb it retained the highest levels of moisture and the best shape after 16 hours of wear. High definition optics ensure you can always see clearly by reducing halos and glare, especially in bright sunshine or low-light. This is combined with a special UV filter to block out harmful levels of sunlight. However, Biotrue ONEday is not a substitute for a good pair of sunglasses.

    Biotrue ONEday has been created to reflect human biology and therefore offers an outstanding lens wearing experience suitable for any contact lens wearer who needs correction for long or short-sightedness, partnered with the freedom of a daily wearing pattern. Lenses are available in base curve BC 8.6.

    SPECIAL OFFER: Buy 1 box (30 pcs) and get 10 lenses free! Clariti 1Day contact lenses from CooperVision/Sauflon offer the convenience of a daily disposable combined with the state of the art technology of silicone hydrogel material. The premium advantages of making use of Clariti 1Day daily lenses include:
    Â• The ability to simply dispose of the lenses after wearing means that users can do away with the need to clean or store the contacts.Â
    • The design of the Clariti 1day contact lenses allows perfect vision regardless of the quality of interior or exterior light.
    • ÂThe high water content and ground-breaking WetLoc technology allows maximum hydration for the eyes. This can offer a fully healthy guarantee for the safety, protection and all round comfort of eyes and vision.

    Recommended for anyone who experiences problems with their vision, Clariti 1Day contact lenses are a great way to maximise sight and overall eye comfort. People who spend long hours in front of a computer screen will be among those who experience the full benefit of these technologically advanced corrective lenses. Lenses are available in base curve BC 8.6.

  6. Dailies Aqua Comfort Plus 30 pcs

    Dailies Aqua Comfort Plus are daily disposable contact lenses from Ciba Vision/Alcon, designed to offer high levels of comfort for wear of up to 20 hours a day. Lightstream technology makes the lens ultra-thin in design, this accompanied by triple action moisturising agents helps to keep discomfort at a low and banish dry eye feelings. Blink activated moisture technology also plays a part in keeping the eyes moist during wear. As the name suggests it works by releasing more moisture when the eye blinks to ensure your lenses don't dry out. Because Dailies Aqua Comfort Plus can be worn from morning till night without discomfort, they are recommended for people who spend long hours working in air conditioned and office environments. They are also great for new contact lens wearers who want a comfortable and convenient contact lens wearing experience. Lenses are available in base curve BC 8.7.

     

    Price: â¬20.99

  7. Dailies Total 1 30 pcs

    Dailies Total 1 is the latest contact lens from Alcon/Ciba Vision. Dailies Total 1 is the world's first water gradient contact lens, made from a unique technology that allows the increase of water content from the core to the surface of the lens via a special transition zone. At the centre of the lens the water content is 33%, but on the surface it's 80%, almost matching that of the eyes natural water content. The silicone hydrogel lens material allows 6 times more oxygen to reach the eye's surface than traditional soft daily lenses, making it the best on the market for oxygen permeability. These two factors combined mean unbeatable all day comfort and unprecedented quality from a contact lens. Dailies Total 1 is ideal for you if you need a lens that can be worn from morning until night without any discomfort.
    Lenses are available in base curve BC 8.5.

    CLEARANCE SALE!  New Frequency 1 Day (also known as Biomedics 1 Day Extra) lenses provide greater comfort. New Frequency 1 Day has been designed with comfort in mind. It is a natural evolution of the trusted Frequency 1 day brand and now brings even greater levels of comfort alongside performance and value.  

    Daily disposable lenses are perfect, whether you wear every day, or just every once in a while, for special occasions or when playing sport. You don't have to deal with the hassle of cleaning them at the end of every day, just dispose and wear a new pair the next day. Daily lenses help to promote healthy eyes, with less chance for protein and debris build up. Lenses are available in base curve BC 8.6.

    FreshLook One Day coloured contact lenses from worldwide contact lens manufacturer Ciba Vision are daily disposable coloured contact lenses. That means you can have all the benefits of a daily disposable lens with the added advantage of being able to subtly change the colour of your eyes. FreshLook One Day coloured contact lenses work best by far with lighter coloured eyes. The also enrich natural dark eye colours by adding more depth. FreshLook One Day coloured contact lenses are supremely comfortable because they are true daily lenses, they're brilliantly convenient because you don't need to be stressing about solutions, cleaning and cases – you just throw them away when you've finished with them. Please note we can not guarantee the color result as it is affected by your natural eye color!

  10. MyDay 30 pcs

    CooperVision® MyDay® lenses take silicone hydrogel 1-day lens performance to the next level. That's because only MyDay features Smart Silicone, a revolutionary breakthrough in lens chemistry that brings together everything your eyes need for an exceptional overall 1-day experience: uncompromised comfort and performance, plus the healthy advantages of silicone hydrogel.
    Smart Silicone optimizes oxygen permeability in a lens that's just 4.4% silicon - the lowest percentage of silicon found in a silicone hydrogel, 1-day lens. By using less silicone, Smart Silicone leaves more room in the lens for built-in channels of comfort-enhancing moisture. It also enables a low modulus. In addition, Smart Silicone provides optimal softness while maintaining exceptional handling. 
    To enhance this further, MYDay lenses also offer an advanced design with a smooth lens surface and rounded edge. Not only does this feel much more natural, allowing your eyelids to glide easily over the surface of the lens, but it also makes putting them in and taking them out much easier. Protecting your eyes from the sun is important and the eye care professionals at CooperVision understand this, that's why they've added UV blocking technology. MyDay shields the eyes from up to 85% of UV-A and 96% of UV-B. However, it's worth noting that MyDay are not a substitute for a good pair of sunglasses but rather a good addition.
    Lenses are available in base curve BC 8.4.

    Proclear 1 Day by CooperVision are ideal for people who suffer with dry eyes but want to wear contact lenses for most of the day, with technology that allows them to stay up to 96% hydrated even after 12 hours of wear. Proclear 1 Day are designed to provide exceptional extensive comfort, no matter how long your day. CooperVision have infused them with a unique material called PC Hydration Technology™, which contains natural molecules that attract and bind water to the surface, keeping them moist and leaving them feeling unnoticeable all day long. Lenses are available in base curve BC 8.7.

A thin lens design combined with slow-release packaging solution provides amazing all day comfort and makes them easy to put in. Exceptional clarity from a contact lens, this unique aspherical design reduces halos and blur, so you don't experience any distortion in your vision, no matter what light you're in, or what power you're wearing. Lenses are available in base curve BC 8.6.

  1. Acuvue Oasys 6 pcs

    Acuvue Oasys is a contact lens which uses Hydraclear Plus technology to deliver all day comfort to even the driest eyes. Hydraclear Plus generates a unique wetting agent which maintains the comfort of the contact lens. Acuvue Oasys is also a high UV blocking contact lens which is ideal for wearers who spend a lot of time outdoors. Lenses are available in base curves BC 8.4 and 8.8.

    Acuvue Oasys should be removed and cleaned before going to sleep and it is recommended that they are replaced with a fresh pair every 2-4 weeks. Some patients can wear Acuvue Oasys for one week continuously. However, not all eyes are suited to continuous wear of Acuvue Oasys lenses and only an Optometrist can determine the appropriate wearing schedule for a patient.

  2. Acuvue Oasys for Astigmatism 6 pcs

    Acuvue Oasys for Astigmatism contact lenses offer the highest level of comfort available yet for a toric contact lens from Acuvue. Using Hydraclear Plus technology these contact lenses bring together a moisture rich wetting agent and the advantages of a silicon hydrogel lens for the first time in a lens for astigmatism. Due to this, Acuvue Oasys for Astigmatism contact lenses retain moisture all day long and the soft and flexible material provides greater patient comfort. Acuvue Oasys for Astigmatism also feature an inside-out marker to make sure that the contact lens is always inserted correctly, and they are slightly tinted to help when handling. An added benefit of Acuvue Oasys for Astigmatism contact lenses is the high level of UV protection that is especially useful for wearers who spend much of the time outdoors.

    Acuvue Oasys for Astigmatism contact lenses should be replaced every 2-4 weeks, and may even be worn continuously for 7 days if your Optometrist has advised this.

    NEW! Avaira Vitality is a new generation of Avaira lenses. CooperVision's Avaira Vitality contact lenses are made with silicone hydrogel material, which is considered amongst the healthiest contact lens material available. This is because it allows up to five times more oxygen to pass through the lens than other soft contact lens materials. As a result, your eyes will remain hydrated for longer. This, combined with increased water content, ensures exceptional performance and all day comfort. With Class 1 UV protection, these lenses also help to block the sun's harmful rays. Avaira Vitality should be used in conjunction with sunglasses for UV protection.

    Benefits:
    - Excellent hydration. Silicone hydrogel is a highly breathable material, allowing increased oxygen levels through to your eyes vs. other materials.
    - Protects your eyes. With Class 1 UV protection, these lenses block the sun's harmful rays.
    - All day comfort. Higher water content keeps these lenses smooth and moist.

    Avaira Vitality lenses should be removed and cleaned before going to sleep and it is recommended that they are replaced with a fresh pair every 2-4 weeks.
